---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import PageHeader from "../components/Sections/PageHeader.astro";

const lastUpdated = "12 July 2026";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy - Blue Fox Tours"
  description="How I handle your personal data"
>
  <PageHeader
    title="Privacy Policy"
    subtitle="How I handle your personal data"
    backgroundImage="/uploads/tours-header-bg.jpg"
  />

  <section class="section-y">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-8"><em>Last updated: {lastUpdated}</em></p>

        <p class="text-l text-gray-700 mb-10">
          I keep this simple, because the data I work with is simple: I'm a one-person tour business,
          and I only process the personal data I need to answer your inquiry and run your tour.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold mb-4">1. Who is responsible for your data</h2>
        <p class="text-l text-gray-700 mb-2">The data controller is:</p>
        <p class="text-l text-gray-700 mb-10">
          <strong>Filip Huta – Blue Fox Tours</strong><br />
          Registered address: TODO_ADDRESS<br />
          IČO (Business ID): TODO_ICO<br />
          Email: <a href="mailto:info@bluefoxtours.cz" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700">info@bluefoxtours.cz</a><br />
          Phone: <a href="tel:+420773537656" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700">+420 773 537 656</a>
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold mb-4">2. What data I collect and why</h2>
        <p class="text-l text-gray-700 mb-6">
          <strong>Booking requests and inquiries</strong> (via the contact form, email, or WhatsApp):
          your name, email address, preferred date, group size, chosen tour, and anything you write in
          your message. I use this to reply to you, confirm availability, and arrange your tour.
          Legal basis: performance of a contract, or steps taken at your request before entering into
          one (Art. 6(1)(b) GDPR).
        </p>
        <p class="text-l text-gray-700 mb-6">
          <strong>Tour-related details you volunteer</strong>: things like mobility considerations or
          children's ages, which help me tailor the tour. Legal basis: performance of a contract.
        </p>
        <p class="text-l text-gray-700 mb-6">
          <strong>Allergy and dietary information</strong> (Prague with Children Tour): because this
          tour includes snacks, I ask parents about allergies and dietary restrictions. This is
          health-related data, so I process it only with your explicit consent (Art. 9(2)(a) GDPR),
          use it solely to choose safe snacks for your tour, and delete it after the tour takes place.
          You can withdraw consent at any time before the tour; in that case, no snacks will be offered.
        </p>
        <p class="text-l text-gray-700 mb-6">
          <strong>Payment data</strong>: card payments are processed by SumUp. I never see or store
          your card details — I receive only a confirmation that payment was made. Cash payments
          involve no data processing at all.
        </p>
        <p class="text-l text-gray-700 mb-6">
          <strong>Invoicing and accounting records</strong>: name and billing details on receipts and
          invoices. Legal basis: legal obligation (Art. 6(1)(c) GDPR) under Czech accounting and tax law.
        </p>
        <p class="text-l text-gray-700 mb-10">
          I do not use your data for marketing, I do not send newsletters, and I never sell or share
          your data for advertising.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold mb-4">3. Who else touches the data</h2>
        <p class="text-l text-gray-700 mb-4">
          I use a small number of service providers (processors) to run this website and business:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-l text-gray-700 mb-6 space-y-2">
          <li>
            <strong>Formspree, Inc.</strong> (USA) — delivers contact-form submissions to my email.
            Transfers to the USA are covered by the EU–US Data Privacy Framework and/or Standard
            Contractual Clauses.
          </li>
          <li><strong>TODO_HOSTING_PROVIDER</strong> — hosts this website.</li>
          <li><strong>TODO_EMAIL_PROVIDER</strong> — my email service.</li>
          <li><strong>SumUp Limited</strong> (Ireland) — card payment processing.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-l text-gray-700 mb-10">
          If you book my tours through third-party platforms (such as Viator or GetYourGuide), those
          platforms are independent data controllers, and their own privacy policies apply to the data
          you give them.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold mb-4">4. How long I keep it</h2>
        <p class="text-l text-gray-700 mb-10">
          Inquiries that don't lead to a booking: deleted no later than one year after our last contact.
          Booking correspondence: kept up to three years after your tour (the limitation period for
          potential claims). Accounting and tax records: retained for the period required by Czech law.
          Children's allergy information: deleted after the tour.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold mb-4">5. Cookies</h2>
        <p class="text-l text-gray-700 mb-10">
          This website sets no tracking or analytics cookies and uses no advertising technology. There
          is nothing to consent to, which is why you don't see a cookie banner.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold mb-4">6. Your rights</h2>
        <p class="text-l text-gray-700 mb-6">
          Under the GDPR you have the right to access your data, correct it, have it erased, restrict
          its processing, object to processing, receive it in a portable format, and withdraw any
          consent you've given. To exercise any of these, just email me at
          <a href="mailto:info@bluefoxtours.cz" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700">info@bluefoxtours.cz</a>
          — I'm the only person who will handle your request, and I'll respond within one month.
        </p>
        <p class="text-l text-gray-700 mb-10">
          You also have the right to lodge a complaint with the Czech supervisory authority:
          <strong>Úřad pro ochranu osobních údajů (ÚOOÚ)</strong>, Pplk. Sochora 27, 170 00 Praha 7,
          <a href="https://www.uoou.gov.cz" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-700">www.uoou.gov.cz</a>.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold mb-4">7. Changes</h2>
        <p class="text-l text-gray-700">
          If I change how I handle personal data (for example, by adding analytics or a newsletter),
          I will update this policy and the date above before the change takes effect.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
